==Korean==
===Verb===
'''물다''' (''mulda'')
# To [[bite]], [[gnaw]]
# To [[bite]], [[sting]]
# To [[bite]], [[swallow]] (''bait'') 
# To [[bite]], [[take hold]] (''in the mouth'')
# To [[bite]], [[mate]], [[mesh]], [[gear]]  
# To [[bite]], [[mate]], [[couple]] (''unduly, deceptively'') 

====Synonyms====
*[[깨물다]] (''kkaemulda'') To [[gnaw]]
*[[쏘다]] (''ssoda'') To [[sting]]
*[[삼키다]] (''samkida'') To [[swallow]] (''bait'') 
*[[머금다]] (''meogeumda'') To [[take hold]] (''in the mouth'')
*[[맞물다]] (''majmulda, mat-'') To [[mate]], [[mesh]]
*[[차지하다]] (''chajihada'') To [[possess]] (''unduly'')

====Antonyms====
*[[놓다]] (''nohda, notda'') To [[lay down]], [[put down]]
*[[뱉다]] (''baetda'') To [[spew]], [[spit]]

====Derived terms====
; Prefixes
*[[물어떼다]] (''murEoTteda'') (''cf. Latin [[mordere]]'') To [[bite]] [[off]]
*[[물어뜯다]] (''murEoTteudda, -Tteutda'') To [[bite]] [[off]]
; Suffixes
*[[깨물다]] (''kkaemulda'') To [[bite]] [[hard]], [[bite]] [[off]], [[gnaw]]
*[[맞물다]] (''majmulda, mat-'') To [[mate]], [[mesh]]
*[[다물다]] (''damulda'') To [[shut]] (''mouth''), [[clamp]] (''lips'')  
*[[아물다]] (''amulda'') To [[heal]] [[up]] (''wound'') 
*[[악물다]] (''agmulda, ak-'') To [[clench]] (''teeth''), compress (''lips''), [[hold]] [[firm]] (''jaws'')

